CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 2, 1955, pg. 27 reads: "11. WHOD broadcast nightly from the fair. In and out of their name-brand stocked booth were Disc Jockey Mary Dee, Newscaster Mal Goode and shown here, Disc Jockey Walt Harper."
TitMainTitle: Walt Harper displaying record to group of men and women with Trower Tailor Company shopping bags, in WHOD radio station booth in Syria Mosque for 1955 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
